lenders.name: yogajr
lenders.loan_because: Yoga makes the ancient practice of yoga fun and friendly for today’s kids. Founded by Lisa Goldberg, a Registered Yoga Teacher (RYT) with Yoga Alliance, with advanced certification in kids yoga, a B.A. in Child Psychology, and more than fifteen years experience working with children, the program’s innovative curriculum combines the benefits of traditional yoga practice, a modern understanding of early childhood development, and an underlying appreciation that kids just want to have fun. : ) Classes are child-centered and play-based, so kids discover yoga and fitness through song, story and play. The goal of Yoga Jr is not only to teach yoga, but to help each child develop self-confidence, patience, and a loving kindness for themselves and others. The kids are also empowered to share their own ideas,which are incorporated in poses and play, building their self-esteem and sense of self. It’s a fun, entertaining and safe way to develop fitness habits, a positive sense of self and respect for others that can last a lifetime.
